{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870569526,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2257d9001KtC3Y1gERnLxor","messageID":"msg_d7a222ba9001QYqYqF2KvbHDot","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_functions.grep:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"valkey|Valkey|AR-014","path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 515 matches (showing first 100)\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n  Line 13: AR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n  Line 17: ## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n  Line 21: | 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct | File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds | 0.5h |\n  Line 22: | 4.1.2 | Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` | Struct fields align with valkey-go ClientOption | 0.5h |\n  Line 23: | 4.1.3 | Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor | Returns Store interface implementation | 0.5h |\n  Line 24: | 4.1.4 | Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment parsing | `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | 0.5h |\n  Line 27: **Deliverable:** Valkey store structure compiles with proper configuration.\n  Line 31: ## ST-4.2 — Valkey Core Store Methods\n  Line 42: **Deliverable:** All core CRUD operations work with Valkey backend.\n  Line 46: ## ST-4.3 — Valkey Index Management Methods\n  Line 59: ## ST-4.4 — Valkey Error Handling