ror | 0.5h |\n  Line 97: | 4.6.3 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordOptional` — success when VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false | Allows empty password | 0.5h |\n  Line 98: | 4.6.4 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MultipleAddresses` — comma-separated VALKEY_ADDR parsing | Splits and trims addresses | 0.5h |\n  Line 99: | 4.6.5 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_DisableCache` — parse VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | Sets DisableCache field | 0.5h |\n  Line 100: | 4.6.6 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_ForceSingle` — parse VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | Sets ForceSingleClient field | 0.5h |\n  Line 101: | 4.6.7 | Write `TestNewValkeyStore` — integration with makeValkeyOptions | Returns valid Store interface | 0.5h |\n  Line 111: | 4.7.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` with testcontainers | Setup real Valkey container | 1.5h |\n  Line 117: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance.\n  Line 125: | 4.8.1 | Add package-level GoDoc for valkey.go | `go doc ./pkg/store` shows Valkey implementation | 0.5h |\n  Line 126: | 4.8.2 | Document `valkeyStore` struct with inline comments | Clear explanation of fields | 0.5h |\n  Line 142: | ST-4.5: Unit Tests (Valkey) | 10 | 10h |\n  Line 152: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey.go` — Valkey Store implementation\n  Line 153: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` — Valkey unit tests\n  Line 154: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` — Valkey integration tests\n  Line 167: # Valkey-specific tests\n  Line 168: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey -v\n  Line 171: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestMakeValkey -v\n  Line 188: - [ ] `valkeyStore` implements full `Store` interface\n  Line 189: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for valkey.go)\n  Line 191: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey\n  Line 203: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` v1.0.56\n  Line 213: - **Error translation:** `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现\n  Line 298:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n  Line 395: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n  Line 400: type valkeyStore struct {\n  Line 401:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n  Line 410: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n  Line 413: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n  Line 414:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n  Line 415:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n  Line 421: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n  Line 429: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n  Line 433: | Method | Valkey API |\n  Line 436: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n  Line 450: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n  Line 457: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n  Line 458: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n  Line 466: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n  Line 471: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n  Line 474: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n  Line 484: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n  Line 524: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n  Line 535: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n  Line 551: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n  Line 566: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n  Line 571: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n  Line 5: **AR ID:** AR-014  \n  Line 11: The Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n  Line 17: ### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n  Line 19: The system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n  Line 21: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n  Line 22: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n  Line 23: - **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 29: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n  Line 30: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n  Line 31: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 35: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n  Line 37: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 43: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n  Line 44: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n  Line 45: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 47: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error())` as true\n  Line 50: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n  Line 52: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 55: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n  Line 57: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n  Line 59: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 62: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n  Line 64: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n  Line 66: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n  Line 69: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n  Line 71: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 515 matches (415 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":515,"truncated":true},"title":"valkey|Valkey|AR-014","time":{"start":1775870569503,"end":1775870569524}}}}
