{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870569552,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2253a1001Zkh0FgLHsb8x7S","messageID":"msg_d7a222ba9001QYqYqF2KvbHDot","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/singleton.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/singleton.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package store\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \t\"fmt\"\n21: \t\"os\"\n22: \t\"strconv\"\n23: \t\"strings\"\n24: \t\"sync\"\n25: \n26: \t\"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n27: )\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \tredisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n31: \tvalkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n32: \n33: \tsessionPrefix        string = \"session:\"\n34: \texpiryIndexKey       string = \"session:expiry\"\n35: \tlastActivityIndexKey string = \"session:last_activity\"\n36: )\n37: \n38: // redisOptions holds Redis connection configuration.\n39: type redisOptions struct {\n40: \tAddr     string\n41: \tPassword string\n42: }\n43: \n44: // valkeyOptions holds Valkey connection configuration.\n45: type valkeyOptions struct {\n46: \tInitAddress       []string\n47: \tPassword          string\n48: \tDisableCache      bool\n49: \tForceSingleClient bool\n50: }\n51: \n52: var (\n53: \tinitStoreOnce sync.Once\n54: \tstoreInstance Store\n55: \tinitError     error\n56: )\n57: \n58: // Storage returns the singleton Store instance.\n59: // Initializes on first call using sync.Once for thread safety.\n60: // Fatals via klog.Fatal if initialization fails.\n61: func Storage() Store {\n62: \tinitStoreOnce.Do(func() {\n63: \t\tstoreInstance, initError = initStore()\n64: \t\tif initError != nil {\n65: \t\t\tklog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", initError)\n66: \t\t}\n67: \t})\n68: \treturn storeInstance\n69: }\n70: \n71: // initStore creates the appropriate Store implementation based on STORE_TYPE env var.\n72: // Returns an error if the store type is unsupported or if required environment\n73: // variables are missing.\n74: func initStore() (Store, error) {\n75: \tstoreType := strings.ToLower(strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"STORE_TYPE\")))\n76: \tif storeType == \"\" {\n77: \t\tstoreType = redisStoreType\n78: \t}\n79: \n80: \tswitch storeType {\n81: \tcase redisStoreType:\n82: \t\treturn newRedisStore()\n83: \tcase valkeyStoreType:\n84: \t\treturn newValkeyStore()\n85: \tdefault:\n86: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported store type: %s (supported: redis, valkey)\", storeType)\n87: \t}\n88: }\n89: \n90: // makeRedisOptions creates redis.Options from environment variables.\n91: // Required: REDIS_ADDR\n92: // Required: REDIS_PASSWORD (unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false)\n93: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisOptions, error) {\n94: \taddr := strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\"))\n95: \tif addr == \"\" {\n96: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n97: \t}\n98: \n99: \tpassword := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n100: \tpasswordRequiredStr := strings.ToLower(strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\")))\n101: \tpasswordRequired := true\n102: \tif passwordRequiredStr != \"\" {\n103: \t\tparsed, err := strconv.ParseBool(passwordRequiredStr)\n104: \t\tif err == nil {\n105: \t\t\tpasswordRequired = parsed\n106: \t\t}\n107: \t}\n108: \n109: \tif passwordRequired && password == \"\" {\n110: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"REDIS_PASSWORD is required (set REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n111: \t}\n112: \n113: \treturn &redisOptions{\n114: \t\tAddr:     addr,\n115: \t\tPassword: password,\n116: \t}, nil\n117: }\n118: \n119: // makeValkeyOptions creates valkey.ClientOption from environment variables.\n120: // Required: VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated addresses)\n121: // Required: VALKEY_PASSWORD (unless VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false)\n122: // Optional: VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE, VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\n123: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkeyOptions, error) {\n124: \taddrStr := strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\"))\n125: \tif addrStr == \"\" {\n126: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n127: \t}\n128: \n129: \taddresses := strings.Split(addrStr, \",\")\n130: \tfor i, addr := range addresses {\n131: \t\taddresses[i] = strings.TrimSpace(addr)\n132: \t}\n133: \n134: \tpassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n135: \tpasswordRequiredStr := strings.ToLower(strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\")))\n136: \tpasswordRequired := true\n137: \tif passwordRequiredStr != \"\" {\n138: \t\tparsed, err := strconv.ParseBool(passwordRequiredStr)\n139: \t\tif err == nil {\n140: \t\t\tpasswordRequired = parsed\n141: \t\t}\n142: \t}\n143: \n144: \tif passwordRequired && password == \"\" {\n145: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n146: \t}\n147: \n148: \topts := &valkeyOptions{\n149: \t\tInitAddress: addresses,\n150: \t\tPassword:    password,\n151: \t}\n152: \n153: \tdisableCacheStr := strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"))\n154: \tif disableCacheStr != \"\" {\n155: \t\tparsed, err := strconv.ParseBool(disableCacheStr)\n156: \t\tif err == nil {\n157: \t\t\topts.DisableCache = parsed\n158: \t\t}\n159: \t}\n160: \n161: \tforceSingleStr := strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"))\n162: \tif forceSingleStr != \"\" {\n163: \t\tparsed, err := strconv.ParseBool(forceSingleStr)\n164: \t\tif err == nil {\n165: \t\t\topts.ForceSingleClient = parsed\n166: \t\t}\n167: \t}\n168: \n169: \treturn opts, nil\n170: }\n\n(End of file - total 170 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/singleton.go","time":{"start":1775870569490,"end":1775870569549}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775870569582,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a226c4f001RWxWjX051s5XnH","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a222ba9001QYqYqF2KvbHDot","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":34651,"input":4,"output":306,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":16248,"read":18093}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775870573312,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a227afd0017475NFDDcthEuE","messageID":"msg_d7a226c90001Y3FdF1L3h1jCs4","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775870574998,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a228032001mNNJ0Mbl7hmwjW","messageID":"msg_d7a226c90001Y3FdF1L3h1jCs4","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"text","text":"Now let me read the full AR-014 delta-spec to understand all requirements:","time":{"start":1775870574997,"end":1775870574997}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870577627,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a228197001Q3Ln5BzmgZKf3U","messageID":"msg_d7a226c90001Y3FdF1L3h1jCs4","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:10","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-014  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n10: \n11: The Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n22: - **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n23: - **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n24: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command using `B().Ping().Build()`\n26: - **AND** require string response `PONG`\n27: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n30: - **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n31: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n32: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n36: - **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n37: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n38: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123` using `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`\n40: - **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n41: - **AND** return `nil` error\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n44: - **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n45: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n46: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `valkey.IsValkeyNil(result.Error())` as true\n48: - **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n51: - **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n52: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n53: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n54: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n55: - **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n58: - **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n59: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n60: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n61: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n62: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n65: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n66: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n67: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n68: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n69: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n72: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n73: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n74: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n75: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n76: - **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses atomic DoMulti\n79: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n80: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n81: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n82: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n83:   - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Nx().Build()`\n84:   - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n85:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(now), sandbox.SessionID).Build()`\n86: - **AND** all commands SHALL succeed for the operation to complete\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n89: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n90: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n91: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n92: - **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL indicate key exists (return value other than \"OK\")\n93: - **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n96: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n97: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist in Valkey\n98: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n100: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX` using `B().Set().Key(key).Value(string(data)).Xx().Build()`\n101: - **AND** return error indicating \"key not exists\" if key does not exist (result not \"OK\")\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n104: - **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n105: - **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists in Valkey\n106: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n107: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n108: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n109: - **AND** update the JSON value\n110: - **AND** return `nil` error\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session and indexes\n113: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` exists\n114: - **AND** `session:expiry` has member `sess-1`\n115: - **AND** `session:last_activity` has member `sess-1`\n116: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n117: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n118: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a single `DoMulti` call:\n119:   - `DEL session:sess-1` using `B().Del().Key(key).Build()`\n120:   - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1` using `B().Zrem().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n121:   - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1` using `B().Zrem().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Member(sessionID).Build()`\n122: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n123: \n124: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n125: - **GIVEN** `session:expiry` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n126: - **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n127: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n128: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with limit > 0\n129: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()}` using `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n130: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n131: - **AND** return results ordered by expiry time (ascending)\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n134: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance\n135: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit is called\n136: - **THEN** return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n139: - **GIVEN** `session:last_activity` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n140: - **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n141: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n142: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called with limit > 0\n143: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()}` using `B().Zrangebyscore().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).Min(\"-inf\").Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix())).Limit(0, limit).Build()`\n144: - **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n145: - **AND** return results ordered by last activity time (ascending)\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns nil for limit <= 0\n148: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance\n149: - **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)` or negative limit is called\n150: - **THEN** return `nil, nil` without querying Valkey\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity updates ZSET\n153: - **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n154: - **AND** current time is `now`\n155: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n156: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n157: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL first verify key exists using `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n158: - **AND** if exists returns 1, execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1` using `B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().ScoreMember(float64(at.Unix()), sessionID).Build()`\n159: - **AND** return `nil` error on success\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity returns ErrNotFound for missing session\n162: - **GIVEN** no session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n163: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n164: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n165: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify key exists using `B().Exists().Key(key).Build()`\n166: - **AND** when exists returns 0, return `ErrNotFound`\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity uses current time when at is zero\n169: - **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n170: - **AND** zero time `time.Time{}` is passed as `at` parameter\n171: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n172: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", time.Time{})` is called\n173: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `time.Now()` as the activity timestamp\n174: - **AND** execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1`\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connections\n177: - **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connections\n178: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n179: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL call `s.cli.Close()`\n180: - **AND** return `nil`\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Valkey loadSandboxesBySessionIDs tolerates orphaned entries\n183: - **GIVEN** a list of session IDs from ZSET query including orphaned entries (no corresponding session key)\n184: - **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n185: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, sessionIDs)` is called\n186: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL use `MGET` with all session keys using `B().Mget().Key(keys...).Build()`\n187: - **AND** skip entries where `v.ToString()` returns error or empty string\n188: - **AND** return only valid sandbox entries without error\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### Requirement: Valkey Configuration\n193: \n194: The system SHALL read Valkey configuration from environment variables and create appropriate client options.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Valkey ADDR is required\n197: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is not set\n198: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n199: - **THEN** return error indicating `VALKEY_ADDR is required`\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Valkey ADDR supports multiple addresses\n202: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=\"host1:6379,host2:6379,host3:6379\"`\n203: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n204: - **THEN** return `InitAddress` as `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\", \"host3:6379\"}`\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n207: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n208: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n209: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not set\n210: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n211: - **THEN** return error indicating `VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Valkey password can be disabled\n214: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set\n215: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty\n216: - **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n217: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n218: - **THEN** return options with empty password and no error\n219: \n220: #### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option\n221: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n222: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n223: - **THEN** return options with `DisableCache: true`\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option\n226: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n227: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n228: - **THEN** return options with `ForceSingleClient: true`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Valkey password parsing is case-insensitive for REQUIRED\n231: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=FALSE` or `False` or `false`\n232: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` is called\n233: - **THEN** treat as password not required\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Requirement: Provider Selection\n238: \n239: The system SHALL support runtime selection between Redis and Valkey backends via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Default to Redis when STORE_TYPE is unset\n242: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` environment variable is not set\n243: - **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n244: - **THEN** default store type is `redis`\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Select Valkey when STORE_TYPE=valkey\n247: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey` (case-insensitive)\n248: - **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n249: - **THEN** create and return `valkeyStore` instance\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: Reject unsupported store type\n252: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=unsupported`\n253: - **WHEN** `initStore()` is called\n254: - **THEN** return error indicating `unsupported store type: unsupported (supported: redis, valkey)`\n255: \n256: ---\n257: \n258: ## Configuration\n259: \n260: ### Environment Variables\n261: \n262: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n263: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n264: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Storage backend type (`redis` or `valkey`) |\n265: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey server addresses |\n266: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | - | Valkey authentication password |\n267: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to allow empty password |\n268: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side caching |\n269: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode |\n270: \n271: ---\n272: \n273: ## Dependencies\n274: \n275: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` - Valkey Go client (v1.0.0+)\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Implementation Notes\n280: \n281: - Valkey is Redis-compatible, so the command patterns mirror Redis implementation\n282: - The `valkey-go` client uses a builder pattern (`B()`) for constructing commands\n283: - Pipeline/Multi operations use `DoMulti()` for atomic execution\n284: - Nil checks use `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` instead of `redis.Nil`\n285: - String results use `result.ToString()` instead of direct string conversion\n286: - Array results from `ZRANGEBYSCORE` use `result.ToArray()` then iterate with `v.ToString()`\n287: - MGET results use `result.ToArray()` and skip entries where `ToString()` returns error\n288: - All ZSET scores use Unix timestamp (seconds since epoch) as float64\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Key Differences from Redis Implementation\n293: \n294: | Aspect | Redis (go-redis/v9) | Valkey (valkey-go) |\n295: |--------|---------------------|-------------------|\n296: | Client creation | `redis.NewClient(opts)` | `valkey.NewClient(opt)` |\n297: | Command building | Direct methods | Builder pattern `B().Cmd().Build()` |\n298: | Pipelines | `Pipeline()` + `Exec()` | `DoMulti()` |\n299: | Nil check | `err == redis.Nil` | `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` |\n300: | Get result | `.Result()` string | `.ToString()` on result |\n301: | Array result | Direct slice | `.ToArray()` then `.ToString()` |\n302: | Close | Returns error | Returns nil |\n\n(End of file - total 302 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [session-store/spec.md](../../session-store/spec.md)\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete Store implementation using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775870577613,"end":1775870577625}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870577630,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2286b600121VGz2CgZ3ltnf","messageID":"msg_d7a226c90001Y3FdF1L3h1jCs4","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n2: \n3: > **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n4: > **Language:** Go  \n5: > **Size:** S  \n6: > **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n7: > **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Overview\n12: \n13: AR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n18: \n19: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n20: |---|------|--------------|------|\n21: | 4.1.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey.go` with `valkeyStore` struct | File compiles; `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds | 0.5h |\n22: | 4.1.2 | Define `valkeyOptions` struct with `InitAddress []string`, `Password`, `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` | Struct fields align with valkey-go ClientOption | 0.5h |\n23: | 4.1.3 | Implement `newValkeyStore()` constructor | Returns Store interface implementation | 0.5h |\n24: | 4.1.4 | Implement `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment parsing | `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | 0.5h |\n25: | 4.1.5 | Add `sessionKey()` helper method for key construction | Returns `session:{id}` format | 0.25h |\n26: \n27: **Deliverable:** Valkey store structure compiles with proper configuration.\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## ST-4.2 — Valkey Core Store Methods\n32: \n33: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n34: |---|------|--------------|------|\n35: | 4.2.1 | Implement `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` | Returns nil on \"PONG\" response; returns error on failure | 0.5h |\n36: | 4.2.2 | Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Returns `ErrNotFound` for missing keys; validates empty sessionID | 1h |\n37: | 4.2.3 | Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic operation: SET NX + ZADD expiry + ZADD last_activity | 1h |\n38: | 4.2.4 | Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error` | Uses SET XX flag; returns error if key doesn't exist | 0.5h |\n39: | 4.2.5 | Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error` | Uses `DoMulti` atomic: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity | 0.5h |\n40: | 4.2.6 | Implement `Close() error` | Calls `s.cli.Close()`; returns nil | 0.25h |\n41: \n42: **Deliverable:** All core CRUD operations work with Valkey backend.\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## ST-4.3 — Valkey Index Management Methods\n47: \n48: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n49: |---|------|--------------|------|\n50: | 4.3.1 | Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:expiry`; returns nil if limit <= 0 | 1h |\n51: | 4.3.2 | Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` | Uses `ZRANGEBYSCORE` on `session:last_activity` | 1h |\n52: | 4.3.3 | Implement `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper | Uses `MGET` for batch fetch; skips orphaned entries gracefully | 1h |\n53: | 4.3.4 | Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` | Checks EXISTS first; uses `time.Now()` if at.IsZero() | 0.5h |\n54: \n55: **Deliverable:** Index operations support session lifecycle management.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## ST-4.4 — Valkey Error Handling\n60: \n61: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n62: |---|------|--------------|------|\n63: | 4.4.1 | Translate `valkey.IsValkeyNil()` to `ErrNotFound` | Unit test: missing key returns `ErrNotFound` | 0.5h |\n64: | 4.4.2 | Handle SET NX failure (session already exists) | Returns \"session already exists\" error | 0.5h |\n65: | 4.4.3 | Handle SET XX failure (key not exists) | Returns \"key not exists\" error | 0.5h |\n66: | 4.4.4 | Handle `DoMulti` partial failures | Returns error from first failed command | 0.5h |\n67: \n68: **Deliverable:** Error handling consistent with Redis implementation.\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## ST-4.5 — Unit Tests — Valkey Implementation\n73: \n74: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n75: |---|------|--------------|------|\n76: | 4.5.1 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Ping` — success and failure | Mock valkey-go client; verify \"PONG\" parsing | 1h |\n77: | 4.5.2 | Write `TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID` — validation, not found, success | Verify `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` translation | 1h |\n78: | 4.5.3 | Write `TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox` — validation (nil, empty ID, zero ExpiresAt), success, duplicate | Verify atomic `DoMulti` with SET NX + ZADD x2 | 1.5h |\n79: | 4.5.4 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox` — validation, missing key, success | Verify SET XX behavior | 1h |\n80: | 4.5.5 | Write `TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — validation, success, idempotent | Verify atomic cleanup of session + indexes | 1h |\n81: | 4.5.6 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes` — limit <= 0, expired sessions, limit applied | Verify `ZRANGEBYSCORE` + `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` | 1h |\n82: | 4.5.7 | Write `TestValkeyStore_ListInactiveSandboxes` — inactive sessions | Similar to expired tests | 1h |\n83: | 4.5.8 | Write `TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity` — validation, not found, zero time, specific time | Verify EXISTS check + ZADD | 1h |\n84: | 4.5.9 | Write `TestValkeyStore_LoadSandboxesBySessionIDs` — empty, orphaned entries, batch load | Verify MGET + orphan skipping | 1h |\n85: | 4.5.10 | Write `TestValkeyStore_Close` — connection release | Verify `cli.Close()` called | 0.5h |\n86: \n87: **Deliverable:** `go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey` passes with >80% coverage.\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ## ST-4.6 — Unit Tests — Configuration\n92: \n93: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n94: |---|------|--------------|------|\n95: | 4.6.1 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MissingAddr` — error when VALKEY_ADDR unset | Returns error | 0.5h |\n96: | 4.6.2 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordRequired` — error when password required but missing | Returns error | 0.5h |\n97: | 4.6.3 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_PasswordOptional` — success when VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false | Allows empty password | 0.5h |\n98: | 4.6.4 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_MultipleAddresses` — comma-separated VALKEY_ADDR parsing | Splits and trims addresses | 0.5h |\n99: | 4.6.5 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_DisableCache` — parse VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | Sets DisableCache field | 0.5h |\n100: | 4.6.6 | Write `TestMakeValkeyOptions_ForceSingle` — parse VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | Sets ForceSingleClient field | 0.5h |\n101: | 4.6.7 | Write `TestNewValkeyStore` — integration with makeValkeyOptions | Returns valid Store interface | 0.5h |\n102: \n103: **Deliverable:** Configuration tests pass with environment variable isolation.\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## ST-4.7 — Integration Tests\n108: \n109: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n110: |---|------|--------------|------|\n111: | 4.7.1 | Create `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` with testcontainers | Setup real Valkey container | 1.5h |\n112: | 4.7.2 | Write end-to-end CRUD test — full lifecycle | Store → Get → Update → Delete | 1h |\n113: | 4.7.3 | Write index consistency test | Verify ZSETs maintained correctly | 1h |\n114: | 4.7.4 | Write concurrent access safety test | 10 concurrent operations, no race | 1h |\n115: | 4.7.5 | Write orphaned entry tolerance test | Delete session data, verify list skips gracefully | 1h |\n116: \n117: **Deliverable:** Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance.\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: ## ST-4.8 — Documentation\n122: \n123: | # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n124: |---|------|--------------|------|\n125: | 4.8.1 | Add package-level GoDoc for valkey.go | `go doc ./pkg/store` shows Valkey implementation | 0.5h |\n126: | 4.8.2 | Document `valkeyStore` struct with inline comments | Clear explanation of fields | 0.5h |\n127: | 4.8.3 | Document each method with purpose and behavior | Godoc format comments | 0.5h |\n128: | 4.8.4 | Add environment variable documentation | List all VALKEY_* variables | 0.5h |\n129: \n130: **Deliverable:** Code is well-documented for future maintainers.\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## Summary\n135: \n136: | Phase | Tasks | Est. Hours |\n137: |-------|-------|------------|\n138: | ST-4.1: Core Structure | 5 | 2.25h |\n139: | ST-4.2: Core Methods | 6 | 3.75h |\n140: | ST-4.3: Index Management | 4 | 3h |\n141: | ST-4.4: Error Handling | 4 | 2h |\n142: | ST-4.5: Unit Tests (Valkey) | 10 | 10h |\n143: | ST-4.6: Unit Tests (Config) | 7 | 3.5h |\n144: | ST-4.7: Integration Tests | 5 | 5.5h |\n145: | ST-4.8: Documentation | 4 | 2h |\n146: | **Total** | **45** | **32h** |\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## File Deliverables Checklist\n151: \n152: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey.go` — Valkey Store implementation\n153: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_test.go` — Valkey unit tests\n154: - [ ] `pkg/store/valkey_integration_test.go` — Valkey integration tests\n155: \n156: ---\n157: \n158: ## Verification Commands\n159: \n160: ```bash\n161: # Build verification\n162: go build ./pkg/store/...\n163: \n164: # Unit test verification (all store tests)\n165: go test ./pkg/store/... -v\n166: \n167: # Valkey-specific tests\n168: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestValkey -v\n169: \n170: # Configuration tests\n171: go test ./pkg/store/... -run TestMakeValkey -v\n172: \n173: # Race detection\n174: go test ./pkg/store/... -race\n175: \n176: # Coverage report\n177: go test ./pkg/store/... -cover\n178: \n179: # Integration tests (requires Docker)\n180: go test ./pkg/store/... -tags=integration -v\n181: ```\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## Definition of Done\n186: \n187: - [ ] All 45 tasks complete\n188: - [ ] `valkeyStore` implements full `Store` interface\n189: - [ ] Unit tests pass (>80% coverage for valkey.go)\n190: - [ ] Configuration tests pass\n191: - [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey\n192: - [ ] Race detector clean\n193: - [ ] `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds\n194: - [ ] Documentation complete with GoDoc\n195: \n196: ---\n197: \n198: ## Dependencies\n199: \n200: - AR-012: Store interface definition (`pkg/store/store.go`)\n201: - AR-013: Redis implementation (reference patterns)\n202: - `pkg/common/types` for `SandboxInfo` type\n203: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` v1.0.56\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Design Notes\n208: \n209: - **Key naming:** Uses `session:{id}` prefix consistently\n210: - **Index keys:** `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity` (sorted sets)\n211: - **Atomic operations:** Uses `DoMulti` for multi-command atomicity\n212: - **Orphan tolerance:** List operations skip missing keys without failing\n213: - **Error translation:** `valkey.IsValkeyNil(err)` → `ErrNotFound`\n214: - **Configuration:** Follows same pattern as Redis with VALKEY_* env vars\n\n(End of file - total 214 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-014 — Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation)\n\n> **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** S  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)  \n> **Base Spec:** AR-012 (Store Interface Definition)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-014 implements a Valkey-backed storage provider for the Store interface defined in AR-012. Valkey is an open-source Redis fork that provides high-performance key-value storage with clustering support. This implementation uses the `valkey-go` client library.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Valkey Store Core Structure\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775870577616,"end":1775870577628}}}}
