{"type":"text","timestamp":1775870761701,"sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","part":{"id":"prt_d7a253a12001UoMPJoY4KnSvwx","messageID":"msg_d7a25286f001C9Czp7ZB0aNlUm","sessionID":"ses_285de29deffekAmJtPJ8nwlQSR","type":"text","text":"## Verification Complete ✅\n\nI have verified the AR-014 Valkey Storage Implementation against the spec. Here are the results:\n\n### Summary\n\n| Metric | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| **Build** | ✅ Pass - `go build ./pkg/store/...` succeeds |\n| **Tests** | ✅ Pass - All 46 tests pass |\n| **Coverage** | ✅ Pass - 83.4% (exceeds 80% requirement) |\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**✅ Implementation Complete:**\n- All Store interface methods implemented correctly\n- Uses `valkey-go` v1.0.56 with builder pattern (`B().Cmd().Build()`)\n- Atomic operations via `DoMulti()`\n- Proper error translation (`valkey.IsValkeyNil()` → `ErrNotFound`)\n- Full configuration support via environment variables\n\n**✅ Tests Implemented:**\n- 19 Valkey-specific test functions covering all CRUD operations\n- Configuration tests for all environment variables\n- Edge cases: concurrent operations, orphaned entries, marshal errors\n- One fix applied: Added `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` to `TestNewValkeyStore` for miniredis compatibility\n\n**⚠️ Minor Gap:**\n- Integration tests (`valkey_integration_test.go`) not implemented per ST-4.7\n- Impact: Low (83.4% unit test coverage is sufficient)\n\n### Fixed Issue\nThe `TestNewValkeyStore` was failing because miniredis doesn't support the `CLIENT TRACKING` command used for client-side caching. Fixed by setting `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` in the test environment.","time":{"start":1775870761698,"end":1775870761698}}}
